╭─ Example Problem ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ A park has three colors of flowering crepe myrtle trees planted: red, white, and pink. When they bloom, a third of   │
│ them are pink, but only two are red. Most of them are white. There are 42 crepe myrtle trees in the park. How many   │
│ have white flowers when they bloom?                                                                                  │
╰──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯

[2026-06-20 15:53:05,025][__main__][INFO] - 
╭─ Example Solution ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ The park has 42 / 3 = <<42/3=14>>14 pink crepe myrtle trees.                                                         │
│ It has 2 red trees, so it has 14 + 2 = <<14+2=16>>16 pink and red trees.                                             │
│ Therefore, there are 42 - 16 = <<42-16=26>>26 crepe myrtle trees that have white flowers when they bloom in the      │
│ park.                                                                                                                │
│ #### 26                                                                                                              │
╰──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯

