│ have white flowers when they bloom?                                                                                  │
│ <|im_end|>                                                                                                           │
│ <|im_start|>assistant                                                                                                │
│ To determine the number of white flowering crepe myrtle trees, we can follow these steps:                            │
│                                                                                                                      │
│ 1. **Identify the total number of trees and the proportions given:**                                                 │
│    - Total number of trees = 42                                                                                      │
│    - A third of the trees are pink.                                                                                  │
│    - Two trees are red.                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                      │
│ 2. **Calculate the number of pink trees:**                                                                           │
│    [                                                                                                                 │
│    \text{Number of pink trees} = \frac{1}{3} \times 42 = 14                                                          │
│    \]                                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                      │
│ 3. **Calculate the number of red trees:**                                                                            │
│    [                                                                                                                 │
│    \text{Number of red trees} = 2                                                                                    │
│    \]                                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                      │
│ 4. **Calculate the number of white trees:**                                                                          │
│    - The rest of the trees are white.                                                                                │
│    [                                                                                                                 │
│    \text{Number of white trees} = \text{Total number of trees} - (\text{Number of pink trees} + \text{Number of red  │
│ trees})                                                                                                              │
│    \]                                                                                                                │
│    [                                                                                                                 │
│    \text{Number of white trees} = 42 - (14 + 2) = 42 - 16 = 26                                                       │
│    \]                                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                      │
│ Therefore, the number of white flowering crepe myrtle trees is \(\boxed{26}\).<|im_end|>                             │
